        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1411822005" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9817377528155434757"><b>MY NAME IS LUCY BARTON</b> is a short 200 page novella jam-packed with emotional substance. It&apos;s a story of a daughter who <b>so</b> loves her mother despite her unpleasant childhood, a daughter who <b>so</b> wants the approval and love of her mother in return.<p>As she recovers from surgery complications, a shocked Lucy receives a five day visit from her estranged mother who can <b>only</b> express her feelings by telling stories of old acquaintances and <b>their</b> imperfect lives; and while listening, Lucy Barton revisits her</p></span>
  <span id="freeText9817377528155434757" style="display:none"><b>MY NAME IS LUCY BARTON</b> is a short 200 page novella jam-packed with emotional substance. It's a story of a daughter who <b>so</b> loves her mother despite her unpleasant childhood, a daughter who <b>so</b> wants the approval and love of her mother in return.<p>As she recovers from surgery complications, a shocked Lucy receives a five day visit from her estranged mother who can <b>only</b> express her feelings by telling stories of old acquaintances and <b>their</b> imperfect lives; and while listening, Lucy Barton revisits her own memories of terror, isolation and the "thing" she does not want to remember in order to make peace with herself and her family.</p><p>Interesting and touching read narrated in the form of multiple short stories as with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1736739.Olive_Kitteridge" title="Olive Kitteridge by Elizabeth Strout" rel="nofollow noopener">Olive Kitteridge</a>.</p></span>
  <a data-text-id="9817377528155434757" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
